Program: Outlook
Title: 14/05/2012
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00rdprh
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 15 May 2012
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, in the first of a series of special reports from Spain, Outlook's Marco Silva meets the Spanish veterans who campaigned against Franco's rule and are now protesting against economic austerity. And an Australian woman who killed a pedestrian many years ago, tells Matthew Bannister about the guilt she has felt ever since and the devastating impact it's had on her life. Show less